  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering through several key mechanisms:\n\n1. Global Regulatory Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Standardized international anti-money laundering (AML) protocols\n\n2. Cooperation Mechanisms\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between financial intelligence units\n- Extradition agreements for financial crimes\n- Cross-border investigation collaboration\n\n3. Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- International banking transparency standards\n- Asset disclosure and tracing mechanisms\n\n4. Legal Enforcement\n- Harmonization of criminal definitions\n- Consistent prosecution standards\n- Mutual recognition of financial sanctions\n- Coordinated asset seizure and recovery processes\n\n5. Technological Integration\n- International financial database networks\n- Digital tracking of complex financial transactions\n- Blockchain and cryptocurrency monitoring frameworks\n\nThese intersections create a comprehensive global approach to preventing, detecting, and prosecuting money laundering activities across different jurisdictional boundaries.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific aspects of international money laundering law?",
